message.content: We have $\log_{25}(x-4)=\frac{1}{2}$. Since we have a base of $25$, we can write this equation as $\left(25\right)^{\frac{1}{2}}=x-4$. Simplifying, we have $\sqrt{25}=x-4$ which gives $x=\pm9$. However, $\frac{1}{\log_{x}3}=\frac{1}{\log_{9}3}$ so $x=-9$ is an extraneous solution as $\log_{9}3$ does not exist. Thus, $x=\boxed{9}$.
